The Gillette Company &lt;GS.N> andSweden's Electrolux AB &lt;ELUX.ST> said they would form apartnership to commercialise a new technology developed by theU.S. Firm which uses solar cells to generate electricity.    Electrolux is interested in harnessing the technology toproduce portable domestic appliances and will provide capitaland development contracts for the joint venture.    The two companies are to establish a laboratory outsideBoston to develop what are known as thermophotovoltaic (TPV)technologies that convert hydrocarbon fuels such as gasolineinto light and electricity through the use of solar cells. REUTER&#3;